"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d35b51",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Classic"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"600f8b",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Temperature >38.3 °C (100.9 °F) for at least 3 weeks with at least 1 week of in-hospital investigation",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"a"
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8e0c4e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"or"
]
},
" "
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d1a93e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Temperature >38.3 °C (100.9 °F) for at least 3 weeks that remains undiagnosed after two visits in the ambulatory setting",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"b"
]
},
" or 3 days in the hospital"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"102e1c",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Infection (endocarditis, tuberculosis [extrapulmonary/disseminated], abscess, endemic mycoses), neoplasm (leukemia, lymphoma, renal cell carcinoma, hepatocellular carcinoma), connective tissue disease (adult-onset Still disease, polymyalgia rheumatica, vasculitis, systemic lupus erythematosus, giant cell arteritis), endocrine disorder (hyperthyroidism, subacute thyroiditis), genetic (familial Mediterranean fever), or miscellaneous (drug fever, factitious fever)"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-2 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7bfa89",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Health care–associated"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"57b77e",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Temperature >38.3 °C (100.9 °F) in patients hospitalized ≥3 days (without fever or evidence of potential infection at the time of admission) and negative evaluation for at least 3 days"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3def8d",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Drug fever, septic thrombophlebitis, venous thromboembolism, sinusitis in the setting of a nasogastric tube, chronic sinusitis without a nasogastric tube, postoperative abscess, ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Clostridioides difficile"
]
},
" infection, device- or procedure-related endocarditis"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-3 row-odd"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4a4d01",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Neutropenic"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"7d843a",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Temperature >38.3 °C (100.9 °F) and neutrophil count <500/µL (0.5 × 10",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"9"
]
},
"/L) for >3 days and negative evaluation after 48 hours"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"15a548",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Bacteremia, opportunistic fungal infections (aspergillosis, candidiasis; more common than bacteremia after 7 days), drug fever, venous thromboembolism, underlying malignancy, allograft rejection in transplant; undiagnosed in 40%-60% of cases"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"tr",
"attrs":{
"className":"group_1-4 row-even"
},
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f934c2",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"HIV-associated"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"62c22c",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Temperature >38.3 °C (100.9 °F) for >3 weeks (outpatients) or >3 days (inpatients) in patients with confirmed HIV infection"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"td",
"attrs":{
"rowSpan":"1",
"colSpan":"1"
},
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"64f17b",
"class":"cell txt l",
"children":[
"Primary HIV infection, opportunistic infections (cytomegalovirus, cryptococcosis, tuberculosis, atypical mycobacteria, toxoplasmosis, ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Pneumocystis jirovecii"
]
},
" pneumonia), lymphoma, immune reconstitution inflammatory syndrome"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
}
]
},
